# proxmox-mcp

.env.example — copy to .env and fill in values:

```
PROXMOX_URL=https://10.96.16.19:8006
PROXMOX_VERIFY=false
PROXMOX_MONITOR_TOKEN_ID=zabbix@pve!zabbix
PROXMOX_MONITOR_TOKEN_SECRET=
PROXMOX_ADMIN_TOKEN_ID=homepilot@pve!homepilot
PROXMOX_ADMIN_TOKEN_SECRET=
PROXMOX_ALLOW_ELEVATED=false
PROXMOX_DEFAULT_NODE=pve
```

## Multi-Node Configuration

For multiple Proxmox endpoints, use one of:

### Option A: PROXMOX_ENDPOINTS_JSON env var

```
PROXMOX_ENDPOINTS_JSON={"verify":false,"timeout":30,"endpoints":[{"name":"pve-cluster","url":"https://10.96.16.19:8006","monitor_token_id":"zabbix@pve!zabbix","admin_token_id":"homepilot@pve!homepilot","default_node":"pve"},{"name":"pve-standalone","url":"https://10.96.16.20:8006","monitor_token_id":"monitor@pve2!token","admin_token_id":"admin@pve2!token"}]}
```

### Option B: proxmox_endpoints.json file

Create `proxmox_endpoints.json` (chmod 600):

```json
{
  "verify": false,
  "timeout": 30,
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "name": "pve-cluster",
      "url": "https://10.96.16.19:8006",
      "monitor_token_id": "zabbix@pve!zabbix",
      "admin_token_id": "homepilot@pve!homepilot",
      "default_node": "pve"
    },
    {
      "name": "pve-standalone",
      "url": "https://10.96.16.20:8006",
      "monitor_token_id": "monitor@pve2!token",
      "admin_token_id": "admin@pve2!token"
    }
  ]
}
```

Secrets are NOT stored in JSON. Set per-endpoint env vars:

```
PROXMOX_PVE_CLUSTER_MONITOR_SECRET=xxx
PROXMOX_PVE_CLUSTER_ADMIN_SECRET=yyy
PROXMOX_PVE_STANDALONE_MONITOR_SECRET=aaa
PROXMOX_PVE_STANDALONE_ADMIN_SECRET=bbb
```

Override the JSON file path with `PROXMOX_ENDPOINTS_FILE`.